      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "This can be written to make use of `AsBytes`, actually:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n@@ -472,10 +472,10 @@ struct CustomUintFormatter\r\n         if (v < 0 || v > MAX) throw std::ios_base::failure(\"CustomUintFormatter value out of range\");\r\n         if (BigEndian) {\r\n             uint64_t raw = htobe64(v);\r\n-            s.write({reinterpret_cast<const std::byte*>(&raw) + 8 - Bytes, Bytes});\r\n+            s.write(AsBytes(Span{&raw, 1}).last(Bytes));\r\n         } else {\r\n             uint64_t raw = htole64(v);\r\n-            s.write({reinterpret_cast<const std::byte*>(&raw), Bytes});\r\n+            s.write(AsBytes(Span{&raw, 1}).first(Bytes));\r\n         }\r\n     }\r\n \r\n@@ -485,10 +485,10 @@ struct CustomUintFormatter\r\n         static_assert(std::numeric_limits<U>::max() >= MAX && std::numeric_limits<U>::min() <= 0, \"Assigned type too small\");\r\n         uint64_t raw = 0;\r\n         if (BigEndian) {\r\n-            s.read({reinterpret_cast<std::byte*>(&raw) + 8 - Bytes, Bytes});\r\n+            s.read(AsWritableBytes(Span{&raw, 1}).last(Bytes));\r\n             v = static_cast<I>(be64toh(raw));\r\n         } else {\r\n-            s.read({reinterpret_cast<std::byte*>(&raw), Bytes});\r\n+            s.read(AsWritableBytes(Span{&raw, 1}).first(Bytes));\r\n             v = static_cast<I>(le64toh(raw));\r\n         }\r\n     }\r\n```\r\n",
      "commit_id" : "2109a147406247bb654ee5fb8421a8594919fbd5",
